-- 
Czech Government to Remove CEZ Chief Executive Roman, LN Reports

-- B y   A l a n   C r o s b y
-- 
2011-09-14T17:01:23Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-14/czech-government-to-remove-cez-chief-executive-roman-ln-reports.html
The Czech government has decided to
fire Martin Roman, the chief executive officer of  CEZ AS (CEZ) , the
country’s largest energy producer, Lidove Noviny reported,
citing unnamed person close to Prime Minister Petr Necas.  Roman’s removal will take place in the coming days, and no
later than within a week, the Prague-based newspaper quoted the
person as saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alan Crosby in Prague at 
 Acrosby1@bloomberg.net  